[2026-02-27 14:15] agent:agent-doctor DECISION: Fix agent launch to redirect stdin from /dev/null
  CONTEXT: SIGTTIN root cause confirmed. Claude processes need stdin disconnected from terminal to prevent job-control signals. Also discovered CLAUDECODE=1 env var blocks nested invocations.
  ACTION: Modified run-ctem-swarm.sh: (1) Added `< /dev/null` to agent subshell, (2) Added `unset CLAUDECODE` to self_heal_environment() and agent subshell, (3) Added `trap '' HUP` alongside existing signal traps.
  RESULT: SUCCESS
  ROLLBACK: Revert changes to lines 3809-3827 of run-ctem-swarm.sh

[2026-02-27 14:20] agent:agent-doctor DECISION: Fix watchdog aggressive kill behavior
  CONTEXT: Watchdog was sending CONT→TERM→KILL in 1 second, killing agents that were only temporarily stopped. This compounded the SIGTTIN issue — even if an agent recovered from SIGTTIN, the watchdog would kill it within 1 second.
  ACTION: Modified watchdog to send SIGCONT first, wait 30 seconds, then recheck. Only kills processes that are STILL stopped after 30s grace period.
  RESULT: SUCCESS
  ROLLBACK: Revert watchdog changes at lines 1909-1922 of run-ctem-swarm.sh

